== Romanian ==
=== Noun ===
'''beregată'''
# [[throat]]

=== Etymology ===
Linguist Sorin Olteanu derives it from Daco-Thracian, from the Proto-Indo-European root ''[[*bher-]]'', "to cut", from which ancient Greek [[pharynx]] ("[[throat]]") is also derived.

